  "narrative_arc": "Community of homeless people living in an abandoned Amtrak tunnel under Manhattan's Upper West Side. They built homes — with electricity tapped from above, furniture scavenged from the street, pets, gardens. Singer (himself homeless, living in the tunnel) documents a functioning community in the most extreme environment.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "The tunnel dwellers built a dome from nothing, underground. Layer 8 (Community) is at maximum — they formed a society. Layer 9 (Environment) is extraordinary — the tunnel itself. Their dome reveals that community can exist where all other layers are absent.",
